The paper deals with the analysis of cooperative communications in network MIMO systems, which involves the use of multiple antennas at base stations to serve multiple users. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses tools from stochastic geometry to derive tractable approximations, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper deals with beamforming, which is a technique used in multimedia systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of the system, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT).
